[A reaction rate of 0.8 percent strikes me as pretty small. I think we would all be surprised if we knew the failure rate of our common vaccines, such as the flu.

Swelling at an injection site, while perhaps painful and annoying, happens with many species and many different vaccines.

To vaccinate or not to vaccine is what this article is all about. Lets rephrase it: to live or not to live! The rate of adverse reactions is small compared to the risk in unvaccinated horses of dying from this disease. - Mod.TG

